{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1725,"text":"Hi. I'm here to talk about congestion,"},{"time":4642,"text":"namely road congestion."},{"time":5996,"text":"Road congestion is a pervasive phenomenon."},{"time":8257,"text":"It exists in basically all of the cities all around the world,"},{"time":11117,"text":"which is a little bit surprising when you think about it."},{"time":13065,"text":"I mean, think about how different cities are, actually."},{"time":16028,"text":"I mean, you have the typical European cities,"},{"time":17790,"text":"with a dense urban core, good public transportation"},{"time":20782,"text":"mostly, not a lot of road capacity."},{"time":23237,"text":"But then, on the other hand, you have the American cities."},{"time":25686,"text":"It's moving by itself, okay."},{"time":28477,"text":"Anyway, the American cities:"},{"time":31483,"text":"lots of roads dispersed over large areas,"},{"time":34411,"text":"almost no public transportation."},{"time":35870,"text":"And then you have the emerging world cities,"},{"time":38080,"text":"with a mixed variety of vehicles,"},{"time":39606,"text":"mixed land-use patterns, also rather dispersed"},{"time":42148,"text":"but often with a very dense urban core."},{"time":44747,"text":"And traffic planners all around the world have tried"},{"time":47149,"text":"lots of different measures: dense cities or dispersed cities,"},{"time":50803,"text":"lots of roads or lots of public transport"},{"time":53354,"text":"or lots of bike lanes or more information,"},{"time":56140,"text":"or lots of different things, but nothing seems to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59934,"text":"But all of these attempts have one thing in common."},{"time":62937,"text":"They're basically attempts at figuring out"},{"time":65288,"text":"what people should do instead of rush hour car driving."},{"time":68615,"text":"They're essentially, to a point, attempts at planning"},{"time":71727,"text":"what other people should do, planning their life for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74929,"text":"Now, planning a complex social system"},{"time":77381,"text":"is a very hard thing to do, and let me tell you a story."},{"time":80456,"text":"Back in 1989, when the Berlin Wall fell,"},{"time":83183,"text":"an urban planner in London got a phone call"},{"time":85805,"text":"from a colleague in Moscow saying, basically,"},{"time":88355,"text":"\"Hi, this is Vladimir. I'd like to know,"},{"time":90873,"text":"who's in charge of London's bread supply?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":93895,"text":"And the urban planner in London goes,"},{"time":95548,"text":"\"What do you mean, who's in charge of London's â€”"},{"time":97518,"text":"I mean, no one is in charge.\""},{"time":98789,"text":"\"Oh, but surely someone must be in charge."},{"time":100671,"text":"I mean, it's a very complicated system. Someone must control all of this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":104327,"text":"\"No. No. No one is in charge."},{"time":107433,"text":"I mean, it basically -- I haven't really thought of it."},{"time":110034,"text":"It basically organizes itself.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":112623,"text":"It organizes itself."},{"time":115200,"text":"That's an example of a complex social system"},{"time":118043,"text":"which has the ability of self-organizing,"},{"time":120771,"text":"and this is a very deep insight."},{"time":123359,"text":"When you try to solve really complex social problems,"},{"time":126672,"text":"the right thing to do is most of the time"},{"time":128388,"text":"to create the incentives."},{"time":129979,"text":"You don't plan the details,"},{"time":131923,"text":"and people will figure out what to do,"},{"time":134543,"text":"how to adapt to this new framework."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136403,"text":"And let's now look at how we can use this insight"},{"time":139894,"text":"to combat road congestion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141530,"text":"This is a map of Stockholm, my hometown."},{"time":143762,"text":"Now, Stockholm is a medium-sized city, roughly two million people,"},{"time":147403,"text":"but Stockholm also has lots of water and lots of water"},{"time":150192,"text":"means lots of bridges -- narrow bridges, old bridges --"},{"time":153469,"text":"which means lots of road congestion."},{"time":156504,"text":"And these red dots show the most congested parts,"},{"time":160144,"text":"which are the bridges that lead into the inner city."},{"time":162721,"text":"And then someone came up with the idea that,"},{"time":165247,"text":"apart from good public transport,"},{"time":167084,"text":"apart from spending money on roads,"},{"time":169685,"text":"let's try to charge drivers one or two euros at these bottlenecks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173900,"text":"Now, one or two euros, that isn't really a lot of money,"},{"time":176824,"text":"I mean compared to parking charges and running costs, etc.,"},{"time":179481,"text":"so you would probably expect that car drivers"},{"time":182199,"text":"wouldn't really react to this fairly small charge."},{"time":184637,"text":"You would be wrong."},{"time":185937,"text":"One or two euros was enough to make 20 percent of cars"},{"time":189965,"text":"disappear from rush hours."},{"time":192349,"text":"Now, 20 percent, well, that's a fairly huge figure, you might think,"},{"time":195900,"text":"but you've still got 80 percent left of the problem, right?"},{"time":198107,"text":"Because you still have 80 percent of the traffic."},{"time":199976,"text":"Now, that's also wrong, because traffic happens to be"},{"time":203243,"text":"a nonlinear phenomenon, meaning that"},{"time":205935,"text":"once you reach above a certain capacity threshold"},{"time":209076,"text":"then congestion starts to increase really, really rapidly."},{"time":212244,"text":"But fortunately, it also works the other way around."},{"time":214704,"text":"If you can reduce traffic even somewhat, then congestion"},{"time":218035,"text":"will go down much faster than you might think."},{"time":221664,"text":"Now, congestion charges were introduced in Stockholm"},{"time":224555,"text":"on January 3, 2006, and the first picture here is a picture"},{"time":229159,"text":"of Stockholm, one of the typical streets, January 2."},{"time":233142,"text":"The first day with the congestion charges looked like this."},{"time":236955,"text":"This is what happens when you take away"},{"time":239875,"text":"20 percent of the cars from the streets."},{"time":241940,"text":"You really reduce congestion quite substantially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244650,"text":"But, well, as I said, I mean, car drivers adapt, right?"},{"time":248308,"text":"So after a while they would all come back because they"},{"time":250810,"text":"have sort of gotten used to charges."},{"time":252758,"text":"Wrong again. It's now six and a half years ago"},{"time":256434,"text":"since the congestion charges were introduced in Stockholm,"},{"time":258417,"text":"and we basically have the same low traffic levels still."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262406,"text":"But you see, there's an interesting gap here in the time series"},{"time":264677,"text":"in 2007."},{"time":266140,"text":"Well, the thing is that, the congestion charges,"},{"time":268529,"text":"they were introduced first as a trial, so they were introduced"},{"time":271625,"text":"in January and then abolished again at the end of July,"},{"time":275594,"text":"followed by a referendum, and then they were reintroduced"},{"time":278188,"text":"again in 2007, which of course was a wonderful scientific opportunity."},{"time":282388,"text":"I mean, this was a really fun experiment to start with,"},{"time":286525,"text":"and we actually got to do it twice."},{"time":288306,"text":"And personally, I would like to do this every once a year or so,"},{"time":290415,"text":"but they won't let me do that."},{"time":291903,"text":"But it was fun anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294088,"text":"So, we followed up. What happened?"},{"time":297473,"text":"This is the last day with the congestion charges, July 31,"},{"time":301339,"text":"and you see the same street but now it's summer,"},{"time":303117,"text":"and summer in Stockholm is a very nice"},{"time":304861,"text":"and light time of the year,"},{"time":307111,"text":"and the first day without the congestion charges"},{"time":309954,"text":"looked like this."},{"time":311321,"text":"All the cars were back again, and you even have to admire"},{"time":313984,"text":"the car drivers. They adapt so extremely quickly."},{"time":316894,"text":"The first day they all came back."},{"time":319141,"text":"And this effect hanged on. So 2007 figures looked like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324491,"text":"Now these traffic figures are really exciting"},{"time":326822,"text":"and a little bit surprising and very useful to know,"},{"time":329473,"text":"but I would say that the most surprising slide here"},{"time":332232,"text":"I'm going to show you today is not this one. It's this one."},{"time":336262,"text":"This shows public support for congestion pricing of Stockholm,"},{"time":339593,"text":"and you see that when congestion pricing were introduced"},{"time":342262,"text":"in the beginning of Spring 2006, people were fiercely against it."},{"time":346579,"text":"Seventy percent of the population didn't want this."},{"time":349607,"text":"But what happened when the congestion charges"},{"time":351255,"text":"were there is not what you would expect, that people hated it more and more."},{"time":354716,"text":"No, on the contrary, they changed, up to a point"},{"time":357869,"text":"where we now have 70 percent support for keeping the charges,"},{"time":361570,"text":"meaning that -- I mean, let me repeat that:"},{"time":363411,"text":"70 percent of the population in Stockholm"},{"time":366218,"text":"want to keep a price for something that used to be free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370211,"text":"Okay. So why can that be? Why is that?"},{"time":373837,"text":"Well, think about it this way. Who changed?"},{"time":376837,"text":"I mean, the 20 percent of the car drivers that disappeared,"},{"time":379463,"text":"surely they must be discontent in a way."},{"time":381408,"text":"And where did they go? If we can understand this,"},{"time":383742,"text":"then maybe we can figure out how people can be so happy with this."},{"time":387872,"text":"Well, so we did this huge interview survey"},{"time":390274,"text":"with lots of travel services, and tried to figure out"},{"time":392109,"text":"who changed, and where did they go?"},{"time":393864,"text":"And it turned out that they don't know themselves. (Laughter)"},{"time":398278,"text":"For some reason, the car drivers are --"},{"time":403126,"text":"they are confident they actually drive the same way that they used to do."},{"time":406622,"text":"And why is that? It's because that travel patterns"},{"time":408878,"text":"are much less stable than you might think."},{"time":411277,"text":"Each day, people make new decisions, and people change"},{"time":414108,"text":"and the world changes around them, and each day"},{"time":416533,"text":"all of these decisions are sort of nudged ever so slightly"},{"time":419786,"text":"away from rush hour car driving"},{"time":421753,"text":"in a way that people don't even notice."},{"time":424337,"text":"They're not even aware of this themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426382,"text":"And the other question, who changed their mind?"},{"time":429183,"text":"Who changed their opinion, and why?"},{"time":431149,"text":"So we did another interview survey, tried to figure out"},{"time":433675,"text":"why people changed their mind, and what type of group changed their minds?"},{"time":438051,"text":"And after analyzing the answers, it turned out that"},{"time":440944,"text":"more than half of them believe that they haven't changed their minds."},{"time":444829,"text":"They're actually confident that they have"},{"time":447116,"text":"liked congestion pricing all along."},{"time":449805,"text":"Which means that we are now in a position"},{"time":451524,"text":"where we have reduced traffic across this toll cordon"},{"time":454517,"text":"with 20 percent, and reduced congestion by enormous numbers,"},{"time":457728,"text":"and people aren't even aware that they have changed,"},{"time":461275,"text":"and they honestly believe that they have liked this all along."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465186,"text":"This is the power of nudges when trying to solve"},{"time":468660,"text":"complex social problems, and when you do that,"},{"time":471292,"text":"you shouldn't try to tell people how to adapt."},{"time":474922,"text":"You should just nudge them in the right direction."},{"time":477109,"text":"And if you do it right,"},{"time":478831,"text":"people will actually embrace the change,"},{"time":480883,"text":"and if you do it right, people will actually even like it."},{"time":483945,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}